WEBVTT

00:00:01.333 --> 00:00:04.893
The air smelled smoky and sulfurous.

00:00:04.917 --> 00:00:07.726
I just stepped off
a rickety train to Korba,

00:00:07.750 --> 00:00:10.018
deep in the Indian state of Chhattisgarh,

00:00:10.042 --> 00:00:12.476
and home to a dozen coal power plants

00:00:12.500 --> 00:00:15.309
and India's largest open-pit coal mine.

00:00:15.333 --> 00:00:16.601
There it is,

00:00:16.625 --> 00:00:18.309
a literal hellscape,

00:00:18.333 --> 00:00:22.143
complete with infernal
fires that burn 24/7.

00:00:22.167 --> 00:00:25.476
But, in Korba, coal is life.

00:00:25.500 --> 00:00:27.101
Most people I talked to accepted

00:00:27.125 --> 00:00:30.101
that the coal economy
powers their livelihoods,